IP(1)

NAME
    ip - show and configure IPv4 networking

SYNOPSIS
    ip [show|-a|--all]
    ip addr show
    ip addr add ip/prefix [gateway gw] [dns dns]
    ip addr del|flush|clear
    ip route show
    ip route add default via gw
    ip route del default
    ip dns show|set dns|clear
    ip dhcp|renew|release
    ip set ip [netmask mask] [gateway gw] [dns dns]
    ip ping ip
    ip arp ip

DESCRIPTION
    ip shows or changes the kernel IPv4 configuration. It can configure an
    address, default gateway, DNS server, and DHCP lease state, and can run
    small ICMP and ARP probes.

COMMANDS
    show
    -a, -all, --all
        Show the current configuration. The all forms include more details.

    addr show
        Show the configured IPv4 address and netmask.

    addr add ip/prefix [gateway gw] [dns dns]
    addr set ip/prefix [gateway gw] [dns dns]
        Configure an IPv4 address. gateway, gw, and via are accepted for the
        gateway keyword.

    addr del
    addr flush
    addr clear
        Clear IPv4 configuration.

    route show
        Show the default route.

    route add default via gw
        Set the default gateway.

    route del default
        Clear the default gateway.

    dns show
    dns set dns
    dns clear
        Show, set, or clear the configured DNS server.

    dhcp
    renew
        Request IPv4 configuration via DHCP.

    release
    clear
        Clear IPv4 configuration.

    set ip [netmask mask] [gateway gw] [dns dns]
        Compatibility form for setting address, netmask, gateway, and DNS.

    ping ip
        Send an ICMP echo request.

    arp ip
        Resolve an IPv4 address to a MAC address with ARP.

EXAMPLES
    ip show
    ip --all
    ip addr add 10.0.2.15/24 gateway 10.0.2.2 dns 8.8.8.8
    ip route add default via 10.0.2.2
    ip dhcp
    ip ping 10.0.2.2

SEE ALSO
    ipconfig(1), dhcp(1), netinfo(1), ping(1)
